It’s a good time to invest in dehumidifier, as they help reduce irritants in the home. Abbas Kanani, a pharmacist and health adviser for Chemist Click, says there are many benefits to having one. He says: ‘There are many benefits to having a dehumidifier in your home, with the main one being that they reduce any allergens and irritants in damp areas of your home. ‘Dehumidifiers may also make breathing easier for people who suffer from asthma. ‘Some other benefits being that they reduce mould and mildew, and these can cause reactions such as itching, sneezing, a runny nose and other irritations. ‘They also prevent musty odours, alleviate allergy symptoms, reduce pest related issues and reduce dust mites.’ The good news is, they don’t have to be super costly. These are some of our favourites on the market. Get it for £149.99. With plenty of good reviews and a low energy option, this is a sturdy choice. Get it for £33.99. A smaller size suitable for flats and less airy rooms. Get it for £39.99. A mid-range option that will let you figure out if a dehumidifier works for your home. Get it for £217. A jumbo sized one for large houses. Get it for £199.99. An investment buy for large damp areas. Get it for £213. Stick this in a damp cellar and let it get to work. Get it for £39. Lightweight and small – yet mighty. Get it for £37.99. A silent option, making it good for small spaces in which noise travels. This article contains affiliate links. We may earn a small commission on purchases made through one of these links but this never influences our experts’ opinions. Products are tested and reviewed independently of commercial initiatives. Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk. MORE : These are the hottest gadgets and tech releases of summer 2022 MORE : The best fitness technology buys of 2022 MORE : Best eco-friendly gadgets from sustainable smartphones to upcycled umbrella lamps